<subSubSection pageId="105" pageNumber="106" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="105.[189,1399,267,400]" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">
The taxonomy of the dark-winged 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hindei Thomas" authorityYear="1901" box="[602,719,268,294]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Scotoecus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[602,719,268,294]" italics="true" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">Scotoecus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
forms is not very clear. Pending a revision of this group, 
<bibRefCitation author="Happold" box="[189,369,302,328]" firstAuthor="Happold" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" refId="ref264870" refString="Happold M. &amp; Happold D. 2013. Mammals of Africa Volume IV. Hedgehogs, Shrews and Bats. Bloomsbury, London." type="book" year="2013">Happold (2013</bibRefCitation>
ak: 669) considers all the dark-winged 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hindei Thomas" authorityYear="1901" box="[835,952,303,329]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Scotoecus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[835,952,303,329]" italics="true" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">Scotoecus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to belong to one species: 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="de Winton" baseAuthorityYear="1899" box="[1267,1391,303,329]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Scotoecus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hirundo">
<emphasis box="[1267,1391,303,329]" italics="true" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">S. hirundo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, we follow Ansell &amp; Dowsett (1988: 44), 
<bibRefCitation author="Taylor &amp; Van der Merwe" box="[777,1195,338,365]" firstAuthor="Taylor" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" pagination="64 - 66" refId="ref273641" refString="Taylor P. J. &amp; Van der Merwe M. 1998. Taxonomic notes on dark-winged house bats of the genus Scotoecus Thomas 1901, in Malawi. Durban Museum Novitates 23: 64 - 66. Available from http: // journals. co. za / deliver / fulltext / admn / 23 / 1 / 1578. pdf? itemId = / content / admn / 23 / 1 / AJA 0012723 X _ 1577 &amp; mimeType = pdf &amp; containerItemId = content / journal / admn [accessed 29 Nov. 2017]." type="journal article" year="1998">Taylor &amp; Van der Merwe (1998: 64)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Cotterill" firstAuthor="Cotterill" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" pagination="219 - 223" refId="ref258510" refString="Cotterill F. P. D. 2001 c. New specimens of lesser house bats (Vespertilionidae: Scotoecus) from Mozambique and Zambia. Arnoldia Zimbabwe 10 (20): 219 - 223." type="journal article" year="2001" yearSuffix="c">Cotterill (2001c: 219)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Simmons" box="[300,556,373,400]" firstAuthor="Simmons" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" pagination="312 - 567" refId="ref273235" refString="Simmons N. B. 2005. Order Chiroptera. In: Wilson D. E. &amp; Reeder D. M. (eds) Mammal Species of the World: A Taxonomic and Geographic Reference: 312 - 567. The John Hopkins University Press, Baltimore." type="book chapter" year="2005">Simmons (2005: 464)</bibRefCitation>
in recognizing 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1901" box="[739,841,373,399]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Scotoecus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hindei">
<emphasis box="[739,841,373,399]" italics="true" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">S. hindei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a separate species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="105.[189,1399,438,536]" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1901" box="[189,388,438,465]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Scotoecus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hindei">
<emphasis box="[189,388,438,465]" italics="true" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">Scotoecus hindei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has only been reported twice from the 
<collectingCountry box="[860,925,439,465]" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">DRC</collectingCountry>
: once from the southeast of the country (Kapolowe, Haut-Katanga Province) and once from the northeast (Niangara, Haut-Uélé Province). Both were already mentioned by 
<bibRefCitation author="Hayman" box="[515,814,509,536]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Hayman" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" pagination="1 - 105" refId="ref265860" refString="Hayman R. W., Misonne X. &amp; Verheyen W. N. 1966. The bats of the Congo and of Rwanda and Burundi. Annalen van het Koninklijk Museum voor Midden Afrika, Zoologische Wetenschappen, Ser. 8, 154: 1 - 105." type="journal article" year="1966">
Hayman 
<emphasis box="[621,680,509,535]" italics="true" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">et al.</emphasis>
(1966: 56)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="105.[189,1399,574,741]" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">
Since 
<bibRefCitation author="Happold" box="[260,437,574,600]" firstAuthor="Happold" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" refId="ref264870" refString="Happold M. &amp; Happold D. 2013. Mammals of Africa Volume IV. Hedgehogs, Shrews and Bats. Bloomsbury, London." type="book" year="2013">Happold (2013</bibRefCitation>
ak: 670) doesn’t recognize 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1901" box="[749,822,574,600]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Scotoecus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hindei">
<emphasis box="[749,822,574,600]" italics="true" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">hindei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a separate species, our distribution map cannot be compared with hers. Based on the data in 
<bibRefCitation author="ACR" box="[731,958,609,636]" firstAuthor="ACR" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" refId="ref254905" refString="ACR. 2016. African Chiroptera Report. AfricanBats, Pretoria. Available from http: // www. africanbats. org / index. php / publications / africa-chiroptera-report [accessed 28 Sep. 2017]." type="url" year="2016">ACR (2016: 1283)</bibRefCitation>
. The SDM map suggests a primarily eastern African distribution, from 
<collectingCountry box="[600,680,645,671]" name="Eritrea" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">Eritrea</collectingCountry>
in the north to southern 
<collectingCountry box="[984,1139,645,671]" name="Mozambique" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">Mozambique</collectingCountry>
and northern 
<collectingCountry box="[1310,1367,645,671]" name="South Africa" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">RSA</collectingCountry>
in the south. It extends westwards across the northern part of the 
<collectingCountry box="[963,1026,680,706]" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">DRC</collectingCountry>
, the 
<collectingCountry box="[1089,1394,680,706]" name="Central African Republic" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">Central African Republic</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[189,311,715,741]" name="Cameroon" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">Cameroon</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[368,460,715,741]" name="Nigeria" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">Nigeria</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
